description: Number of partitions of n into parts of 8 kinds.

Index entries for expansions of Product_{k >= 1} (1-x^k)^m
formula: a(n) ~ exp(4 * Pi * sqrt(n/3)) / (sqrt(2) * 3^(9/4) * n^(11/4)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 28 2015
maple: with(numtheory): a:= proc(n) option remember; `if`(n=0, 1, add(add(d*8, d=divisors(j)) *a(n-j), j=1..n)/n) end: seq(a(n), n=0..40); # _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
